The Edo State Police Commissioner, DanMallam Muhammed, has punctured the claims that the residence of the National Chairman of the APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole in Edo was attacked at the weekend. Oshiomhole’s media aide, Simon Ebegbulem had alleged that his boss residence was attacked by thugs sent by the state Governor, Godwin Obaseki But the commissioner said:  “There was no attack on Oshiomole’s residence. He (Oshiomhole) visited the Oba of Benin, we escorted him to the airport and he thanked us for the security of the state,” OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY  Edo APC crisis: Oshiomhole, Obaseki loyalists alleged attack on members Gunmen kill Oshiomhole’s private secretary The unending crisis in Edo Assembly